President Obama spoke with President Dilma Rousseff of Brazil to discuss the spread of the Zika virus in the Western Hemisphere. They agreed on the importance of collaborative efforts to deepen knowledge, advance research, and accelerate work on vaccines and technologies to control the virus. They also discussed the need to prioritize building capacity to combat infectious disease threats. President Rousseff confirmed her attendance at the Nuclear Security Summit in Washington, D.C. and both leaders agreed to work together to make the Summit a success.